    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a peerless 2011 BMW M3 Coupe, a definitive specimen of the E92 platform. At its heart lies the S65 4.0-liter naturally aspirated V8, utilizing eight individual throttle bodies and Double-VANOS high-pressure stepless variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band culminating at an 8,400 RPM redline. This example features the preferred 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock, ensuring mechanical purity and tactile engagement. The chassis is equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC), providing sophisticated compression and rebound management across three distinct modes. Every mechanical component is in superlative order; proactive rod bearing replacement and throttle actuator services have been performed to aerospace standards. The exterior retains its factory depth and luster with no evidence of road rash, while the interior leather maintains its original matte finish and structural integrity, reflecting a vehicle that has been fastidiously preserved in a climate-controlled environment.",
